creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: three vertical ornamental studies, one rectangular, and two more triangular; sinuous vines with thick leaves emerge vertically from ornate ewers at the bottom, each with a slightly different variation

provenance: Ducs d'Arenberg; [C. & J. Goodfriend, New York, until October 17, 1983; sold to Andrus]; John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. title: Ornament with Vase; Two Designs for Sheaths
